To achieve this, I will initiate a program where parents and older students can volunteer to assist in various activities. This could include reading to the children, helping with craft projects, assisting in science experiments, or participating in outdoor games. I will also provide training sessions for volunteers to understand the objectives of these activities and how they can best assist. I will plan these activities in such a way that they encourage children to engage in focused, complex play, which is crucial for their cognitive development.
